Durban - Three people were killed and 19 were injured in several road accidents across KwaZulu-Natal at the weekend.
Yesterday, 15 people were injured after the taxi they were travelling in collided with a vehicle on the M1 Richmond Road in Pinetown.

On Saturday, a 40-year-old runner was killed in an alleged hit-and-run in Winston Park, Hillcrest.
Blue Security spokesperson Andreas Mathios said an officer responded to the scene. “When our officer arrived, he found the victim bleeding from his head and lying near a driveway,” said Mathios. He added that ER24 paramedics declared the man dead at the scene.
On Friday, a pedestrian was seriously injured on the M4 near Ballito. IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson Paul Herbst said it was believed the pedestrian was crossing the road when he was struck by a truck.

In a head-on collision on the N2 before the M25 KwaMashu highway, a woman was killed and a man injured. 
Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said both drivers were trapped in the wreckages.
Just after 9am a woman, aged 60, was killed in a head-on crash near Riverhorse Valley in the same area. 

